<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Flag to allow throwing exceptions from the server.</p>

<p>Example:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>

Sample:
</code></pre>

<p>$server-&gt;throwExceptions(true);
try {
    echo $server-&gt;handle();
} catch (MyPersonalException $e) {
    echo $server-&gt;fault($e);
} catch (Exception $e) {
    // do other things like logging, email the admin as this was an unexpected error.
    echo $server-&gt;fault(new Exception('An unknown error occured. Please try again.'));
}
```</p>

<p>This would bring the server components more inline with the PHP SoapServer API.</p>

